b'Next in our series introducing #HiltonCleanStay, we\xe2\x80\x99d like to share how we\xe2\x80\x99re adapting the lobby area to better serve your needs.\xe2\x81\xa3 \xe2\x81\xa3\nYou\xe2\x80\x99ll notice that furniture has been rearranged to accommodate social distancing, and that hand sanitizer is now available at the front desk and near the elevators. We\xe2\x80\x99ve also introduced a new designated area for 3rd party food delivery drop-offs in most properties, so that you can get your favorite restaurant meals without needing to interact with a delivery person.'

b"Monday we shared how the #HiltonCleanStay seal lets you know your guest room has been professionally deep cleaned. But just what does that entail?\n\nWorking with health and safety experts, we identified the 10 hot spots that will receive extra attention from our housekeeping staff prior to every check-in. That's a cleaning you can trust."

b'Today we\xe2\x80\x99re kicking off a series dedicated to sharing all about our Hilton CleanStay program, so that you can feel confident when you stay with us. \xe2\x81\xa3\n\xe2\x81\xa3\nLet\xe2\x80\x99s start with the Hilton CleanStay seal. When guests first enter their room, the seal lets them know that their room was professionally deep cleaned since the last guest \xe2\x80\x94 and that no one has entered their room since that cleaning. #HiltonCleanStay'

b'At Hilton, we have been listening to and learning from our Team Members and Guests to convert the gravity of this moment into meaningful, long-term action against systemic racism. We have been on this journey but know there is more we can do:\xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x81\xa3 \xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x81\xa3
#1. We have activated The Hilton Effect Foundation to further support our partners, the NAACP and the National Urban League, at the front lines of the fight for racial justice.\xc2\xa0\xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x81\xa3
#2. We have adopted measures that will ensure diverse slates of Director candidates and increase the diversity of Hilton\xe2\x80\x99s Board.\xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x81\xa3
#3. We have set leadership diversity targets across our corporate and hotel teams that are tied directly to leadership compensation and must be met by 2025.\xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x81\xa3
#4. We are expanding on our universal Unconscious Bias and Inclusive & Respectful Workforce training for all of our employees.\xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x81\xa3
#5. We invite our 106M Hilton Honors members and Team Members to join us by donating Hilton Honors points to social justice charities of your choice through PointWorthy; we convert donated points into a cash contribution to support these organizations.
Thank you to our Team Members and Guests who have reached out to share their experiences. We will keep looking for ways that Hilton hospitality can make the world a better place, and can help bring communities closer together. #BlackLivesMatter'
